|ElectoralVotes = 10 |State Animal = Horseshoe crab }}  'Maryland' () For those who distinguish them, Maryland is
pronounced as in merry , not as in the name Mary . (Random House
Dictionary) is a U.S. state located in the Mid-Atlantic region of the
United States, bordering Virginia, West Virginia, and the District of Columbia
to its south and west; Pennsylvania to its north; and Delaware to its east.
Maryland was the seventh state to ratify the United States Constitution, and has
three occasionally used nicknames: the Old Line State, the Free State, and the
Chesapeake Bay State.

Maryland is one of the smallest states in terms of area, but it remains one of
the most populous and the most densely populated states of the United States.
The state's largest city is Baltimore, and its capital is Annapolis. The state
was either named after Queen Henrietta Maria or Mary, the mother of Jesus
Christ. (The original intent by Cecilius Calvert is unknown.) Of
the 50 U.S. states, Maryland has the highest median household income, making
it the wealthiest state in the nation. {{cite web
|url=http://proximityone.com/stmhi0910.htm |title=State Median Household
Income Patterns: 1990-2010 |publisher=U.S. Census Bureau |accessdate=2012-08-
06 }}

Ethnically, the majority of Marylanders are of German and Irish descent, though
the state has a large group of African Americans.
